cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with model compression for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and specifically focuses on image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end learning method for weight sampling, which involves optimizing the network architecture and sampling rules simultaneously. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions using neural architecture search (NAS) based methods as a baseline, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper reports results on ImageNet, which is a large-scale image dataset, indicating that it may also belong to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
